    [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### Motivation\n- Wire the file tree drag-and-drop action to a real backend move operation and enforce vault-relative path rules to prevent accidental or malicious moves.\n\n### Description\n- Add `moveFile` frontend command wrapper in `src/lib/commands/editor.ts` and its signature to `src/app.d.ts` to invoke a new `move_file` Tauri command. \n- Implement `moveFile` in the files store (`src/lib/stores/files.svelte.ts`) as `moveFileEntry` with `normalizeVaultRelativePath`, `findFileEntry`, and `validateMove` helpers to ensure vault-relative paths, reject traversal/absolute paths, prevent same-path moves, and disallow moving a folder into itself or its descendants. \n- Register and handle `file:move` drag-and-drop events in `src/lib/components/App.svelte` to call `files.moveFile(detail.oldPath, detail.newPath)` and announce the move. \n- Add a backend `move_file` command and `normalize_vault_relative_path` helper in `src-tauri/src/commands/editor.rs`, update `resolve_vault_path` to canonicalize the vault root, and register `move_file` in the Tauri invoke handler (`src-tauri/src/lib.rs`) to perform server-side validation and the filesystem `rename`. \n\n### Testing\n- Ran `pnpm typecheck` (`tsc --noEmit`), which succeeded. \n- Ran `pnpm lint`, which failed due to missing ESLint flat config in the environment (ESLint v10 config issue). \n- Ran `cargo check` in `src-tauri`, which failed in this environment due to a missing system dependency (`glib-2.0` pkg-config), not code errors in the changes themselves.\n\n------\n[Codex Task](https://chatgpt.com/codex/cloud/tasks/task_e_6a2838cca92883219e7facb8cd9c5175)"[m[1;37m,[m
