    [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### Motivation\n- Support per-provider configuration records (API key, base URL, default model, enabled state) instead of relying on a single global AI config when building AI clients.\n- Allow the frontend to pass a provider identifier to backend commands and resolve the actual configured provider record server-side.\n\n### Description\n- Add shared provider models on the Rust side: `ProviderConfig` and `ProviderInput` in `src-tauri/src/types.rs`, and extend `Provider` to include `anthropic/google/custom` aliases to match frontend shape.\n- Persist provider records in `AIConfig.providers` with a default Ollama entry and add a migration helper `Config::ensure_provider_records()` to convert legacy scalar AI fields; update `src-tauri/src/config.rs` accordingly.\n- Update AI commands in `src-tauri/src/commands/ai.rs` to accept `ProviderInput`, resolve the matching configured `ProviderConfig` (erroring when missing or disabled), and construct provider clients using the configured `api_key`, `base_url`, `default_model`, `temperature`, and `max_tokens` values.\n- Expose `get_providers` and `save_providers` Tauri commands in `src-tauri/src/commands/config.rs` and register `get_providers`/`save_providers` in the invoke handler in `src-tauri/src/lib.rs`.\n- Align frontend types and bindings: add `ProviderType` and update `ProviderConfig` in `src/lib/types.ts`, change `testProviderConnection` in `src/lib/commands/ai.ts` to pass the provider ID string, and update `src/app.d.ts` to reflect the new invoke signatures.\n\n### Testing\n- Ran `pnpm typecheck` (`tsc --noEmit`) which succeeded.\n- Ran `git diff --check` which reported no invocation-blocking issues for the changed files.\n- Attempted `cargo check --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml` which failed due to a missing system dependency (`glib-2.0` / `glib-2.0.pc`) in the environment, blocking a full Rust build verification.\n- Ran `cargo fmt --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml -- --check` which reported formatting differences in the repository unrelated to the functional changes in this patch.\n\n------\n[Codex Task](https://chatgpt.com/codex/cloud/tasks/task_e_6a2838c9cce08321bf6d3329ea2528fa)"[m[1;37m,[m
