    [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### Motivation\n- Ensure the AI chat backend and frontend agree on the streaming event shape and return type so streaming works reliably. \n- Allow frontend to send minimal `ChatMessage` objects (role/content) without breaking backend deserialization. \n\n### Description\n- Emit plain text chunks on the unified `ai:chunk` event and send each non-empty token as the event payload via `app.emit(\"ai:chunk\", content)`. \n- Accumulate streamed tokens server-side and make `ai_chat` return the final assistant text as `Result<String, String>` to match the frontend `Promise<string>` contract. \n- Make `ChatMessage` deserialization tolerant by defaulting missing `timestamp` with `chrono::Utc::now` and adding a `#[serde(default)]` for `model`. \n\n### Testing\n- Ran `pnpm typecheck` / `tsc --noEmit`, which completed successfully. \n- Ran `rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src-tauri/src/commands/ai.rs src-tauri/src/types.rs`, which succeeded. \n- Attempted `cargo check --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml`, which could not complete in this environment due to a missing system `glib-2.0` pkg-config dependency.\n\n------\n[Codex Task](https://chatgpt.com/codex/cloud/tasks/task_e_6a2838c839a4832188bf38ee124648c3)"[m[1;37m,[m
