    [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### Motivation\n- Simplify the UI contract by returning plain tag names instead of name/count tuples so front-end components can render and search tags without needing tuple handling.\n- Preserve ordering by counts on the backend while exposing a simple `Vec<String>` for Tauri invocations.\n\n### Description\n- Changed Rust `get_tags` signature to return `Result<Vec<String>, String>` and updated implementation to sort tags by count (desc) with a deterministic name tie-breaker, then map to a `Vec<String>`; file modified: `src-tauri/src/commands/editor.rs`.\n- Typed the Tauri wrapper `getTags()` invocation as `invoke<string[]>('get_tags')` in `src/lib/commands/editor.ts` so TypeScript expects an array of strings.\n- Updated the files store to assign typed tag names in `loadTags()` (`src/lib/stores/files.svelte.ts`) by using `.then((tagNames: string[]) => { tags = tagNames; })`.\n- Updated the sidebar tag rendering to iterate `files.tags` as `tagName` and call `files.searchFiles(tagName)` when a tag chip is clicked in `src/lib/components/Sidebar.svelte`.\n\n### Testing\n- Ran `pnpm typecheck` which succeeded.\n- Ran `git diff --check` which succeeded with no new issues from this change.\n- Ran `cargo fmt --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml --check` which reported rustfmt drift unrelated to the functional change (existing formatting diffs outside this patch).\n- Ran `cargo check --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml` which failed in this environment due to a missing system dependency (`glib-2.0`) and not due to the code changes.\n\n------\n[Codex Task](https://chatgpt.com/codex/cloud/tasks/task_e_6a2838c40008832185b29fc7c9be8b14)"[m[1;37m,[m
