    [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### Motivation\n- Consolidate the recent-files response into a dedicated shared shape so both backend and frontend agree on the returned structure. \n- Ensure recent items include useful metadata (`modified`) and expose vault-relative paths for consistent client-side navigation. \n- Make UI usage explicit (select + open) and display timestamp info for better UX when choosing recent files.\n\n### Description\n- Added a Rust `RecentFile` struct with `name`, `path`, and `modified` and updated `get_recent_files` to return `Result<Vec<RecentFile>, String>` while producing vault-relative, POSIX-normalized paths and converting file modification times to `chrono::DateTime<chrono::Utc>` (`src-tauri/src/types.rs`, `src-tauri/src/commands/editor.rs`).\n- Introduced `vault_relative_path` helper to compute vault-relative paths and normalize separators (`src-tauri/src/commands/editor.rs`).\n- Added a matching TypeScript `RecentFile` interface and updated the Tauri command wrapper `getRecentFiles` to return `Promise<RecentFile[]>` (`src/lib/types.ts`, `src/lib/commands/editor.ts`).\n- Updated the files store to use `RecentFile[]` and updated the Sidebar UI to select the file before opening and show the `modified` timestamp in the item title (`src/lib/stores/files.svelte.ts`, `src/lib/components/Sidebar.svelte`).\n\n### Testing\n- Ran `pnpm typecheck` (`tsc --noEmit`) which completed successfully. \n- Ran `git diff --check` which reported no issues. \n- Attempted `cargo check` for the Rust side but it failed due to a missing system dependency (`glib-2.0`/`glib-2.0.pc` not available to `pkg-config`), so full Rust compile verification is blocked by that environment requirement. \n- Ran `cargo fmt` as part of checks (no formatting errors reported).\n\n------\n[Codex Task](https://chatgpt.com/codex/cloud/tasks/task_e_6a2838c22f108321a3c05e3c24f5097a)"[m[1;37m,[m
