    [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### Motivation\n- Prevent path traversal and unsafe paths from reaching filesystem operations by validating user-provided paths early. \n- Ensure consistent comparisons by canonicalizing the vault root once and resolving targets relative to that canonical root. \n- Allow creating new files safely by resolving the nearest existing parent for non-existent targets. \n\n### Description\n- Parse `user_path` components in `src-tauri/src/commands/editor.rs::resolve_vault_path` and reject `..`, absolute/root components, `Component::Prefix`, and Windows-style prefixes via a new `has_windows_prefix` helper. \n- Canonicalize the vault root once into `canonical_root` and join validated relative components to form candidate targets. \n- For non-existent targets, canonicalize the nearest existing parent and append the validated missing components to produce the final `PathBuf`. \n- Add unit tests in the same file covering `\"../outside.md\"`, `\"/tmp/file.md\"`, `r\"C:\\\\tmp\\\\file.md\"`, a nested existing path (`notes/daily/today.md`), and a non-existent valid file (`notes/new.md`). \n\n### Testing\n- Ran `cargo fmt --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml` which completed successfully. \n- Ran `cargo test -p zs-note resolves_ --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml` which could not run due to a missing system dependency (`glib-2.0` / `glib-2.0.pc`). \n- Also attempted `cargo test --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml --lib resolves_ --no-default-features` which was blocked for the same missing system package.\n\n------\n[Codex Task](https://chatgpt.com/codex/cloud/tasks/task_e_6a2838c08d4083218e7be22c32e3a358)"[m[1;37m,[m
