    [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### Motivation\n- Ensure all editor-related Tauri commands receive vault-relative, forward-slash paths for portability and to avoid mixing absolute filesystem paths with frontend file IDs.\n- Make recent-file responses match the frontend `FileEntry` shape so UI components can consume entries consistently.\n\n### Description\n- Backend: changed `list_files` to produce `FileEntry` records with `path` converted to a vault-relative, `/`-joined string and added `vault_relative_path` helper; updated `get_recent_files` to return `Vec<FileEntry>` with the same shape; replaced the enum `FileEntry` with a serializable struct (`name`, `path`, `is_dir`, optional `children`, optional `extension`).\n- Frontend commands: added `src/lib/utils/vaultPath.ts::toVaultRelativePath` and updated `src/lib/commands/editor.ts` to normalize all path arguments passed to Tauri invocations.\n- UI wiring: updated `FileTree.svelte`, `Sidebar.svelte`, and `src/lib/stores/editor.svelte.ts` so they pass vault-relative paths for open/save/create/rename/delete/drag-drop and when populating recent files.\n\n### Testing\n- Ran `pnpm typecheck` (invokes `tsc --noEmit`) which completed successfully.\n- Ran Svelte diagnostics via `pnpm exec svelte-check` which reported existing Svelte/TS errors and warnings across the app (not introduced by this change). \n- Ran Rust formatting (`rustfmt` / `cargo fmt`) successfully; attempted `cargo check --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml` but it was blocked by a missing system `glib-2.0` pkg-config dependency in the environment.\n\n------\n[Codex Task](https://chatgpt.com/codex/cloud/tasks/task_e_6a2838be2f788321946e27a66ba09923)"[m[1;37m,[m
