    [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### Motivation\n- Ensure the Settings UI uses the existing backend config commands instead of ad-hoc per-field save calls so settings persist correctly and missing-command failures are visible. \n- Simplify save/load semantics by round-tripping a single backend `Config` object to avoid inconsistent partial updates and brittle `.catch(() => defaults)` fallbacks. \n- Surface load/save errors in the Settings UI so developer errors are not silently ignored during development. \n\n### Description\n- Registered the Tauri commands `commands::config::get_config`, `commands::config::update_config`, `commands::config::reset_config`, and `commands::config::reload_config` in `src-tauri/src/lib.rs`. \n- Reworked `src/lib/stores/config.svelte.ts` to introduce a `BackendConfig` shape, keep a `currentConfig`, add `applyBackendConfig` and `buildConfigForSave`, load via `invoke('get_config')`, and save via `invoke('update_config', { newConfig })` through a new `saveAll` helper. \n- Replaced granular `save_*` invoke calls with `saveAll()` by changing `saveEditorSettings`, `saveVaultConfig`, `saveProviders`, `saveSandboxConfig`, `saveSyncConfig`, `savePublishTargets`, and `saveImageHost` to call the unified save, and removed the broad `.catch(() => defaults)` fallback on load. \n- Updated `src/lib/components/Settings.svelte` to call `config.saveAll()` from the modal save path and to surface store errors via a `displayedError` binding, and updated `src/app.d.ts` Tauri typings to reflect `get_config`, `update_config`, `reset_config`, and `reload_config`. \n\n### Testing\n- Ran `pnpm typecheck` (`tsc --noEmit`) which completed without TypeScript errors. \n- Ran `git diff --check` which reported no whitespace or diff issues. \n- Ran `cargo check` which failed due to a missing system dependency (`glib-2.0` / missing `glib-2.0.pc`) in the environment and is therefore blocked, not a code regression. \n- Ran `cargo fmt --check` which flagged existing rustfmt differences in unrelated Rust files in this environment (pre-existing), not caused by the config wiring changes.\n\n------\n[Codex Task](https://chatgpt.com/codex/cloud/tasks/task_e_6a2838c56dfc8321a7fed801a00e405c)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Streamlined internal configuration management by consolidating settings operations through a unified backend interface. Configuration loading and saving now route through a centralized system, improving efficiency and maintainability while preserving all existing functionality and user experience.\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->"[m[1;37m,[m
